Description: Small wall sherd of East Greek (North Ionian?) pottery cup; interior glazed; exterior: broad band painted at top of fragment, where turn of lip is just preserved; inscription cut on exterior, below painted band.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Sanctuary of Apollo (Naukratis) (said to be)
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.375)
